To cover the else block in the `parse` method where the value is replaced with an empty string, you can add the following JUnit 5 test case:

```java
@Test
void parseWithNonExistentAttributeName() throws Exception {
    String expression = "%attribute1:nonExistent%";
    srcMap.put("details", Map.of("name", "John"));

    String result = alarmPostingUtils.parse(expression, srcMap, "");

    assertEquals("", result);
}
```

In this test case, the expression `%attribute1:nonExistent%` specifies an attribute that does not exist in the source map. As a result, the `else` block inside the `parse` method will be executed, replacing the value with an empty string. This test case will provide coverage for that part of the code.